## Today's Goals

* Graph rational functions and identify key features including asymptotes and intercepts.
* Find zeros and point discontinuities.
* Analyze real-world scenarios modeled by rational functions.

## Vocabulary

* **Rational Function** — A function of the form [f(x) = P(x)/Q(x)] where [P] and [Q] are polynomials and [Q(x) ≠ 0].
* **Zeros of a Function** — The [x]-values that make the function equal to zero.
* **Point Discontinuity** — A hole in the graph where the function can be simplified.
* **End Behavior** — What happens to the function values as [x] approaches positive or negative infinity.
* **Oblique Asymptote** — A slanted asymptote that occurs when the degree of the numerator is one more than the degree of the denominator.

